From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [ldn_mitm] Integrate switch-lan-play relay bridge (lanplay_bridge)

Wire ldn_mitm into the switch-lan-play relay so that "wireless local" games
(those intercepted by ldn_mitm) work over the internet:

 1. lanplay_bridge.{hpp,cpp} — reads sdmc:/tmp/lanplay.status to discover
    the virtual IP that switch-lan-play has assigned.

 2. getFakeMac() / getNodeInfo() use the virtual IP (10.13.x.y) instead of
    the real WiFi IP so that station-to-AP connections use the relay path.

 3. getBroadcast() returns the virtual subnet broadcast (10.13.255.255) so
    Scan packets travel through the relay rather than over the real WiFi.

 4. initialize() skips nifmSetLocalNetworkMode(true) when switch-lan-play
    is active; that call disables internet access which would sever the
    relay UDP connection.

Apply with: patch -p1 -d ldn_mitm < patches/0001-lanplay-bridge.patch

diff --git a/ldn_mitm/source/lan_discovery.cpp b/ldn_mitm/source/lan_discovery.cpp
index 30b77d0..45c0cbe 100644
--- a/ldn_mitm/source/lan_discovery.cpp
+++ b/ldn_mitm/source/lan_discovery.cpp
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@
